A suspected serial killer, Oluwatosin Ikuemehinlo, known in the underworld as 4G, has been arrested by detectives in Ondo State. Oluwatosin allegedly terrorised residents of Okitipupa and Igbokoda areas of the state, even said to behind for many deaths in the communities. It was gathered that he was arrested in Okitipupa after policemen in the area were tipped off about his presence.   Security operatives take down 200 bandits in Niger     Man charged with selling six kids     Brent oil hits $112 on Russian crude ban   A police source said, “The alias, 4G, means that the suspect’s network never fails. Besides, he had killed many people in the area, cutting their bodies to pieces. He was suspected to have been selling human parts to ritualists, and he always recorded and shared the dismembered bodies on social media. “Security agencies are doing exactly what the people of Ilaje want. This is what we have been expecting from our security men, I think they are doing well now, and still expecting more from them for peace to return permanently to our community.” Police spokeswoman, Funmilayo Odunlami, said she was yet to have details of Oluwatosin’s arrest.